  <descriptions>
    <description descriptionType="Abstract">The Palmer Penguins dataset is an introductory biology dataset containing measurements for 344 penguins from three species observed on three islands in the Palmer Archipelago, Antarctica. The simplified penguins table includes species, island, bill length, bill depth, flipper length, body mass, sex, and year.</description>
    <description descriptionType="Methods">Data were collected through the Palmer Station Long-Term Ecological Research program and later packaged for teaching and data exploration as the palmerpenguins dataset.</description>
  </descriptions>
